geneSummary: FGFR3, a receptor tyrosine kinase, is altered by mutation, chromosomal rearrangement or amplification in various cancers, most frequently in bladder cancer.

mutationEffect.description: The FGFR3 V677I mutation is located in the kinase domain of the protein. This mutation has been found in intestinal cancer. Expression of this mutation in a murine fibroblast cell line demonstrated that it is neutral as measured by no change in protein activity compared to wildtype (PMID: 26992226)

variantSummary: The FGFR3 V677I mutation is likely neutral.
